 a Silver Age. Timberg’s reporting is essential reading for anyone who works in the world of culture, knows someone who does, or cares about the work creative artists produce.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCreative abilityxHistoryx21st centuryxUnited States. 0aCreative abilityzUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aPopular culturexHistoryx21st centuryxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aPopular culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aSocial changexHistoryx21st centuryxUnited States. 0aSocial changezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aSocial classesxHistoryx21st centuryxUnited States. 0aSocial classeszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021065140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210651423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300210651/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles